&nbsp;<a href="papers.html">Presentations</a><br>
<h3>For OpenBSD</h3>
&nbsp;<a href="ftp.html">Download</a><br>
d25 4
a28 10
<h3>For other OS's</h3>
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">Linux</a>,
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">FreeBSD</a>,<br>
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">NetBSD</a>,
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">Solaris</a>,<br>
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">MacOS X</a>,
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">HP-UX</a>,<br>
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">QNX4</a>,
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">IRIX</a>,<br>
&nbsp;<a href="portable.html">AIX</a><br>
d40 1
a40 1
OpenNTPD is primarily developed by Henning Brauer as
d42 4
a45 2
and gets released as part of it every six months.
<blink>The portable version is outdated and in need of a maintainer.</blink>
a48 11
<p>
Managing the distribution of OpenNTPD is split into two teams.  One
team does strictly OpenBSD-based development, aiming to produce code
that is as clean, simple, and secure as possible. We believe that
simplicity without the portability &quot;goop&quot; allows for better code
quality control and easier review.  The other team then takes the clean
version and makes it portable, by adding the portability &quot;goop&quot;
so that it will run on many operating systems (these are known as the
<strong>p</strong> releases, and named like &quot;OpenNTPD 3.9p1&quot;).
Please click on the provided link for your operating system.
<p>
@


